ecobee, Inc. Key Developments

ecobee, Inc. Presents at 21st-Annual CONNECTIONS: The Premier Connected Home, May-24-2017 10:30 AM
May 20 17
ecobee, Inc. Presents at 21st-Annual CONNECTIONS: The Premier Connected Home, May-24-2017 10:30 AM. Venue: Hyatt Regency, San Francisco Airport, San Francisco, California, United States. Speakers: Stuart Lombard, Founder, Chief Executive Officer and President.


ecobee Launches ecobee4 Smart Thermostat with Built-In Alexa Voice Service
May 3 17
ecobee Inc. announced its next-generation smart thermostat: ecobee4. WithAmazon Alexa voice service and far-field voice recognition, ecobee4 combines smart thermostat functionality and voice to help customers manage their home’s comfort, energy and busy lives. The company also announced plans to bring Alexa and far-field voice recognition to every room of the home through a voice-enabled smart light switch. This product will mark the company’s first venture beyond smart thermostats and is expected to lead the smart home category into a whole-home-voice future. Similar to ecobee’s signature room sensor technology, the smart light switch will measure occupancy and temperature to help deliver comfort in the rooms that matter most. With a built-in speaker and microphone, ecobee4 can be controlled through its sleek touch-screen, a smart device or voice. Alexa voice service allows customers to simply ask their ecobee4 to adjust the temperature of the home, in addition to the growing list of Alexa skills such as setting a timer, helping plan commute or playing the news. Through far-field voice recognition, ecobee4 will conveniently respond to voice commands from anywhere in the room. ecobee4 is also compatible with the company’s signature room sensor technology, which measures occupancy and temperature to deliver comfort when the customer is home and energy savings when they’re away. ecobee4 smart thermostat ($249) will be available on ecobee.com, Amazon.com, Lowes.com, HomeDepot.com and BestBuy.com for pre-order beginning May 3, 2017 and will hit retail shelves on May 15, 2017. The device comes with a wireless room sensor and supports up to 32 sensors.


ecobee Launches New ecobee3 lite Smart Thermostat
Oct 17 16
ecobee, Inc. announced the launch of ecobee3 lite. The new device gives consumers the value on the market, delivering superior comfort, control and energy savings at $80 less than devices from competitors. The device will be available for purchase across North America on October 31, 2016. ecobee3 lite features a beautiful and easy-to-use touchscreen interface and pays for itself in less than a year. ecobee3 lite features a beautiful and easy-to-use touchscreen interface and pays for itself in less than a year. ecobee3 lite also integrates with Amazon Echo, Apple HomeKit, Samsung SmartThings, Wink and IFTTT. The ecobee3 lite launch is accompanied by a new mobile application from ecobee, which will be available on Apple and Android devices. The application includes a new Installation Wizard, providing homeowners with step-by-step installation support and videos in the palm of their hand. ecobee3 lite is designed to be compatible with 95% of residential heating and cooling systems in North America and does not require a C-wire when using the included Power Extender Kit. To ensure ecobee3 lite will work in your home, visit ecobee.com/compatibility.


